1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:56,195 --> 00:00:59,073
FILING FOR LOVE

3
00:01:53,877 --> 00:01:55,045
What kind of dream was that?

4
00:02:05,639 --> 00:02:06,640
Did you get some rest?

5
00:02:07,057 --> 00:02:09,768
Don't forget to come in
at the usual time today. Good luck.

6
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:11,770
Oh, right. Work.

7
00:02:13,981 --> 00:02:15,941
No wonder I had that terrible dream.

8
00:02:31,081 --> 00:02:33,417
Here's your iced Americano.

9
00:02:35,294 --> 00:02:36,336
Mr. Noh.

10
00:02:36,712 --> 00:02:39,047
- Are you okay now?
- What do you mean?

11
00:02:39,131 --> 00:02:41,341
When there was a ruckus outside
two days ago

12
00:02:41,717 --> 00:02:43,635
you passed out in shock.

13
00:02:44,011 --> 00:02:47,598
The photos are everywhere.
They call you the Haemu Fainter.

14
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,601
I heard the affair was real.

15
00:02:50,934 --> 00:02:52,811
So her husband is
Mr. Son from Food Brand Planning?

16
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,481
What happens to them now?

17
00:02:55,689 --> 00:02:58,108
You handle the employees' affairs...

18
00:02:58,192 --> 00:02:59,485
- Da-yeong.
- Yes?

19
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:01,820
I think your orders
are pretty backed up.

20
00:03:02,488 --> 00:03:03,906
I'm so sorry.

21
00:03:08,869 --> 00:03:10,245
Hey, Mr. Noh.

22
00:03:11,038 --> 00:03:12,122
The Haemu Fainter.

23
00:03:13,874 --> 00:03:15,959
You look fine. Are you all right now?

24
00:03:16,043 --> 00:03:17,252
- I'm fine.
- Good.

25
00:03:17,336 --> 00:03:19,963
I heard you're in charge of affairs.
How did that happen?

26
00:03:20,047 --> 00:03:21,799
- I thought you were some big shot.
- Hey.

27
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:24,635
I handle PM cases, not affairs.

28
00:03:24,843 --> 00:03:26,595
And the term is
"personal misconduct."

29
00:03:27,429 --> 00:03:28,597
You're just clueless.

30
00:03:36,522 --> 00:03:37,773
Mr. Noh.

31
00:03:42,694 --> 00:03:43,695
Yes, Ms. Park.

32
00:03:43,987 --> 00:03:46,406
I heard what happened.
Are you all right?

33
00:03:47,407 --> 00:03:48,450
I'm fine.

34
00:03:48,992 --> 00:03:50,118
That's good to hear.

35
00:03:57,835 --> 00:03:59,461
Hey, there, Mr. Noh.

36
00:03:59,962 --> 00:04:01,171
Are you just clocking in?

37
00:04:01,547 --> 00:04:03,590
I'm so pleased to see you,
I could faint.

38
00:04:06,969 --> 00:04:07,970
Ms. Joo.

39
00:04:08,846 --> 00:04:10,639
You can't tease me about that.

40
00:04:11,515 --> 00:04:13,308
Why not? Don't I have the right?

41
00:04:13,642 --> 00:04:16,270
The only reason you're fine
without a single scratch

42
00:04:16,478 --> 00:04:19,439
is that I caught you like this
with my two arms as you fell.

43
00:04:19,857 --> 00:04:21,942
You know I saved you, right?

44
00:04:23,569 --> 00:04:25,320
I sprained my wrist a bit,
so I got some acupuncture.

45
00:04:26,905 --> 00:04:28,323
Sure, I can't thank you enough.

46
00:04:28,615 --> 00:04:29,741
It's nothing, really.

47
00:04:32,119 --> 00:04:34,913
I'll type up a report on what action
to take against Mr. Son.

48
00:04:35,664 --> 00:04:37,291
I took care of that already.

49
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:38,959
What?

50
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,295
I closed that case.

51
00:04:44,965 --> 00:04:47,134
Mouthwatering and mellow,
here's Masigo.

52
00:04:47,551 --> 00:04:50,387
With Haemu's own
innovative food technology

53
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:53,765
Masigo succeeded to realize
the farm-to-table notion

54
00:04:53,849 --> 00:04:55,392
and we're confident it will become

55
00:04:55,475 --> 00:04:58,312
a brand that represents Haemu
and leads global food trends.

56
00:04:58,604 --> 00:05:00,772
That concludes the presentation.
Thanks for listening.

57
00:05:05,277 --> 00:05:06,320
Thank you.

58
00:05:12,784 --> 00:05:13,827
Thank you.

59
00:05:14,119 --> 00:05:15,454
I'll do my best.

60
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:22,878
Even so, that's not right, Ms. Joo.

61
00:05:23,879 --> 00:05:26,924
How could Ms. Jeong be demoted
to a plant while Mr. Son remains?

62
00:05:27,132 --> 00:05:28,800
And he gets to keep his project?

63
00:05:29,885 --> 00:05:32,679
If we must decide who did worse,
Ms. Jeong is single

64
00:05:32,763 --> 00:05:34,431
while Mr. Son's married,
so he did more harm.

65
00:05:34,514 --> 00:05:36,350
Who did Mr. Son cause harm to?

66
00:05:37,601 --> 00:05:39,436
Mr. Son always did well at work

67
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:41,730
and he's in charge of a new brand
the Food Team has invested in.

68
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:43,315
What about Ms. Jeong?

69
00:05:43,398 --> 00:05:45,150
All she did was play a part
in Mr. Son's project.

70
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:46,693
Her performance and reputation
are below his.

71
00:05:47,569 --> 00:05:48,862
From the company's point of view

72
00:05:48,946 --> 00:05:51,281
Ms. Jeong has done more harm
than Mr. Son.

73
00:05:51,865 --> 00:05:52,908
Am I wrong?

74
00:05:54,493 --> 00:05:55,702
Still, morally speaking...

75
00:06:00,499 --> 00:06:01,541
Morals?

76
00:06:02,084 --> 00:06:03,961
Do you think
you're a police officer or a judge?

77
00:06:04,252 --> 00:06:07,047
Do companies reward the good
and punish the bad?

78
00:06:07,339 --> 00:06:09,466
A company only has to care

79
00:06:09,549 --> 00:06:12,010
about the profit or loss
caused by an employee.

80
00:06:12,094 --> 00:06:14,930
Because here,
that is our ethics and morals.

81
00:06:24,356 --> 00:06:25,440
What is it?

82
00:06:25,524 --> 00:06:27,526
Did you hope
for an exhilarating resolution?

83
00:06:28,026 --> 00:06:30,696
For a cheating couple
to be humiliated out of their jobs?

84
00:06:33,281 --> 00:06:34,825
You're more naive than you look.

85
00:06:36,535 --> 00:06:37,828
Why did you put me in charge?

86
00:06:41,123 --> 00:06:42,165
This duty

87
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,377
doesn't suit me because I'm naive.

88
00:06:51,550 --> 00:06:52,676
No, you're perfect for the job.

89
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:55,137
- Ms. Joo, what on earth...
- Don't get too upset.

90
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:57,264
Mr. Son got a bigger percentage
of his pay docked.

91
00:06:57,639 --> 00:07:00,517
Not to mention that this incident
ruined his reputation for good.

92
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,103
It will be taken into consideration
at his next performance review.

93
00:07:03,603 --> 00:07:06,106
Plus, there are legal repercussions
if he's sued for divorce.

94
00:07:08,316 --> 00:07:10,694
There, let's forget
about a closed case.

95
00:07:10,777 --> 00:07:12,362
Do your next assignment right.

96
00:07:12,571 --> 00:07:13,572
Sorry?

97
00:07:17,117 --> 00:07:18,118
"Work.com."

98
00:07:18,618 --> 00:07:20,370
You should check it out.
The comments are insane.

99
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:54,905
EPISODE 2:
I AM THE BEST

100
00:07:55,489 --> 00:07:57,616
Seriously, do something about Zone F.

101
00:07:57,699 --> 00:07:59,367
It's basically a love motel in Haemu.

102
00:07:59,701 --> 00:08:01,578
- It's like watching porn.
- "Zone F"?

103
00:08:01,661 --> 00:08:02,746
So everyone knows it.

104
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,664
The head office's
basement parking lot.

105
00:08:05,248 --> 00:08:07,959
- It probably has no cameras.
- What is this about?

106
00:08:08,043 --> 00:08:09,336
I never park there.

107
00:08:09,419 --> 00:08:10,796
Is this news to you?

108
00:08:12,047 --> 00:08:14,508
It's Zone F in level four
of the basement parking lot.

109
00:08:15,175 --> 00:08:17,177
It's the spot
for couples in the company

110
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:19,137
whether they're dating
morally or immorally.

111
00:08:19,679 --> 00:08:22,557
It's dark with no cameras
pointing that way

112
00:08:22,808 --> 00:08:24,351
and not many park that far down.

113
00:08:24,768 --> 00:08:25,852
It's perfect.

114
00:08:26,103 --> 00:08:28,188
You seem to know a lot, Mr. Cha.

115
00:08:28,271 --> 00:08:30,816
That's what I heard
through the grapevine.

116
00:08:31,691 --> 00:08:33,151
Let's check the facts first.

117
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:35,529
We can't investigate
based on a rumor.

118
00:08:35,612 --> 00:08:36,738
- Yes, sir.
- Okay?

119
00:08:36,822 --> 00:08:38,448
Check facts? With whom?

120
00:08:39,241 --> 00:08:40,867
Our team has set up

121
00:08:40,951 --> 00:08:43,411
- a humint network.
- What? "Humint"?

122
00:08:43,495 --> 00:08:44,538
INFO GATHERED FROM INFORMANTS

123
00:08:44,621 --> 00:08:47,332
- Yes.
- Gosh, don't even talk about it.

124
00:08:47,415 --> 00:08:48,625
There's no end to it.

125
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:51,586
It's embarrassing for both parties
if we catch them in the act.

126
00:08:52,129 --> 00:08:53,630
We just turn a blind eye.

127
00:08:53,713 --> 00:08:56,800
I heard Zone F is the place to go.

128
00:08:56,883 --> 00:09:00,011
BASEMENT PARKING CLOSED
FOR REPAIR WORK

129
00:09:00,095 --> 00:09:01,138
It's that spot over there.

130
00:09:02,013 --> 00:09:04,141
Is it more thrilling
if they do it there?

131
00:09:04,683 --> 00:09:07,144
I don't know why people
with decent jobs would do that.

132
00:09:09,187 --> 00:09:10,480
I wonder myself.

133
00:09:10,564 --> 00:09:12,732
If you see anything suspicious

134
00:09:12,816 --> 00:09:14,109
please report it to us.

135
00:09:14,192 --> 00:09:17,028
- Sure thing. Take care, then.
- Thank you.

136
00:09:19,865 --> 00:09:23,451
Our humint network confirmed
the rumor is true.

137
00:09:27,205 --> 00:09:28,790
Humint, my foot.

138
00:09:30,792 --> 00:09:32,669
- Let's go eat.
- Okay.

139
00:09:32,752 --> 00:09:35,380
The cafeteria's serving pork cutlet,
doenjang soup

140
00:09:35,463 --> 00:09:36,548
- braised potatoes...
- Not there.

141
00:09:36,631 --> 00:09:38,758
I'll check my list
of nearby restaurants.

142
00:09:39,134 --> 00:09:40,385
Don't bother.

143
00:09:45,307 --> 00:09:47,851
THIS EVENING

144
00:09:52,564 --> 00:09:54,232
What are you doing today?
It's your birthday.

145
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,026
Did your boyfriend schedule a date?

146
00:09:56,860 --> 00:09:57,861
Well...

147
00:09:57,944 --> 00:10:00,071
Why are you so mysterious?

148
00:10:00,322 --> 00:10:03,158
I'm curious what kind of guy
girls like you date.

149
00:10:41,321 --> 00:10:43,657
Why does the cafeteria food
get worse by the day?

150
00:10:43,823 --> 00:10:46,243
- Right? Let's eat out tomorrow.
- Okay.

151
00:10:46,534 --> 00:10:47,994
- Ms. Yeon.
- What?

152
00:10:48,078 --> 00:10:50,497
Isn't that Mr. Kwon, your husband?

153
00:10:51,164 --> 00:10:52,374
Yes, that's right.

154
00:10:52,457 --> 00:10:54,167
Why don't you even say hi?

155
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,086
Did you two fight?

156
00:10:57,462 --> 00:10:59,214
We didn't fight. We get along fine.

157
00:10:59,547 --> 00:11:01,633
Ji-yeon, wait until you get married.

158
00:11:01,716 --> 00:11:02,759
After just a few years

159
00:11:03,009 --> 00:11:04,636
you flinch
when your hands accidentally touch.

160
00:11:05,136 --> 00:11:06,179
That's an exaggeration.

161
00:11:09,849 --> 00:11:11,142
You two are hilarious.

162
00:11:11,476 --> 00:11:13,687
Before you got married,
you didn't say hi

163
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:15,105
because you were dating in secret.

164
00:11:15,188 --> 00:11:16,856
But now,
everyone knows you're married.

165
00:11:17,399 --> 00:11:18,692
Are you shy now that you're married?

166
00:11:18,775 --> 00:11:20,318
We're keeping work
and personal lives separate.

167
00:11:21,069 --> 00:11:24,364
You speak as if
your private life is pretty eventful.

168
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,201
Hey.

169
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,203
Do you guys even do it?

170
00:11:30,704 --> 00:11:31,705
Stop it.

171
00:11:32,622 --> 00:11:34,082
You don't do that with family.

172
00:11:36,001 --> 00:11:37,419
You used to be so fired up.

173
00:11:38,211 --> 00:11:39,921
Why does it die
once people get married?

174
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:42,424
You burn to death
if you stay fired up.

175
00:11:51,224 --> 00:11:52,892
NEW MESSAGE FROM YEON
FROM GENERAL AFFAIRS

176
00:11:54,227 --> 00:11:56,354
I'm meeting old friends from school
and will be home late.

177
00:11:57,814 --> 00:11:58,898
Okay.

178
00:12:13,913 --> 00:12:15,749
Oh, dear. I'm so sorry, Mr. Kwon.

179
00:12:16,416 --> 00:12:19,127
- It's okay.
- I'm so stupid.

180
00:12:19,210 --> 00:12:20,962
I'm really sorry.

181
00:12:21,046 --> 00:12:22,797
Don't be. It happens.

182
00:12:24,132 --> 00:12:25,133
Ms. Seon?

183
00:12:25,675 --> 00:12:26,843
I'm coming, sir.

184
00:12:27,385 --> 00:12:28,553
- Sorry.
- Go ahead.

185
00:12:51,409 --> 00:12:53,203
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

186
00:12:58,166 --> 00:12:59,709
I'm loving this.

187
00:13:00,210 --> 00:13:01,336
- Right?
- Jun-seo!

188
00:13:02,003 --> 00:13:04,297
- Over here.
- He looks even better now.

189
00:13:04,381 --> 00:13:06,424
- Long time no see.
- You haven't changed at all.

190
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:09,344
Sorry, I forgot to tell you
he was coming.

191
00:13:10,887 --> 00:13:11,930
Don't worry.

192
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,890
It's been ages since we broke up.

193
00:13:22,273 --> 00:13:23,733
It has been a while, So-young.

194
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:25,110
Yes.

195
00:13:25,318 --> 00:13:27,153
You look just the same.

196
00:13:27,821 --> 00:13:28,863
You haven't changed.

197
00:13:30,156 --> 00:13:32,450
I'm not the same. I got old, right?

198
00:13:32,534 --> 00:13:33,618
No.

199
00:13:33,952 --> 00:13:35,703
You're pretty. Just like before.

200
00:13:36,830 --> 00:13:39,249
- What's going on here?
- You're prettier now.

201
00:13:40,041 --> 00:13:42,252
- You're just the same.
- I lost my appetite.

202
00:13:43,086 --> 00:13:44,671
- Sorry.
- Pour me a drink?

203
00:13:45,171 --> 00:13:46,214
Here.

204
00:13:47,882 --> 00:13:49,008
Let's begin.

205
00:13:55,098 --> 00:13:56,558
You can vote now.

206
00:13:56,641 --> 00:13:58,143
FINAL RESULT
OF THE THIRD SURVIVOR

207
00:13:59,144 --> 00:14:00,353
Why did his ranking drop?

208
00:14:00,437 --> 00:14:03,356
Vote for the person
who stole your heart.

209
00:14:05,275 --> 00:14:07,110
The mission benefit is too great.

210
00:14:07,193 --> 00:14:10,738
BOYS II PLANET's first round
of the final global vote is now open.

211
00:14:11,614 --> 00:14:13,283
BOYS II PLANET's final global...

212
00:14:13,366 --> 00:14:15,076
Can I vote for the same person twice?

213
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,870
Log onto the BOYS II PLANET site

214
00:14:17,829 --> 00:14:18,997
and click "vote"

215
00:14:19,539 --> 00:14:21,666
- then select one participant.
- Who's that?

216
00:14:26,796 --> 00:14:29,090
Hi. Let's have a drink.
It's been a while.

217
00:14:41,603 --> 00:14:43,938
What are you up to?
Do you want to get back with me?

218
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,524
Do you want to?

219
00:14:47,609 --> 00:14:48,735
Forget it, then.

220
00:14:49,903 --> 00:14:52,822
Gosh.
You're really one-sidedly one-sided.

221
00:14:53,448 --> 00:14:55,783
You asked me out
then suddenly ghosted me.

222
00:14:56,409 --> 00:14:58,286
Now you barge in after two years

223
00:14:58,661 --> 00:15:00,288
- and want a drink?
- So what?

224
00:15:00,872 --> 00:15:02,415
Were you sad that I dumped you?

225
00:15:03,249 --> 00:15:04,459
Did you cry over me?

226
00:15:05,335 --> 00:15:06,628
You didn't.

227
00:15:06,711 --> 00:15:09,172
"If you want to leave, go ahead.
I won't hold you back."

228
00:15:09,756 --> 00:15:12,050
I bet you didn't even shed a tear.

229
00:15:12,884 --> 00:15:14,385
Here. have a drink and call it even.

230
00:15:26,147 --> 00:15:27,148
It's good, isn't it?

231
00:15:29,442 --> 00:15:30,610
It's not bad.

232
00:15:32,403 --> 00:15:34,072
Let me stay for a while.

233
00:15:35,573 --> 00:15:37,367
- What?
- Let me stay here.

234
00:15:38,159 --> 00:15:39,452
The whiskey's the rent.

235
00:15:39,869 --> 00:15:41,204
This costs over three million won.

236
00:15:41,287 --> 00:15:43,456
Hey, what kind of nonsense is this?

237
00:15:43,957 --> 00:15:46,000
Get out. This isn't a boarding house.

238
00:15:46,084 --> 00:15:47,919
I really don't have a place to go.

239
00:15:48,169 --> 00:15:51,631
I had to leave my old place
and I couldn't find a new place yet.

240
00:15:51,923 --> 00:15:53,383
You know that my family...

241
00:15:54,384 --> 00:15:56,052
They're no help to me at all.

242
00:15:57,762 --> 00:15:59,305
I get that you're in a tough spot...

243
00:15:59,556 --> 00:16:02,183
You can't barge
into a guy's bachelor pad.

244
00:16:05,061 --> 00:16:06,854
- I'll get you a hotel room.
- For how long?

245
00:16:07,272 --> 00:16:08,815
Who knows how long I'll need?

246
00:16:09,357 --> 00:16:10,483
Do you have ten million won?

247
00:16:15,989 --> 00:16:17,740
I guess you can't help me.

248
00:16:18,408 --> 00:16:20,034
I get it. I'll leave.

249
00:16:20,910 --> 00:16:24,539
I'll stay at a sauna
or end up on some street corner.

250
00:16:24,622 --> 00:16:27,333
And if a creepy guy hits on me?

251
00:16:27,417 --> 00:16:29,335
I'll go with him. I can't be picky.

252
00:16:30,670 --> 00:16:31,713
Goodbye.

253
00:16:42,682 --> 00:16:43,766
It's only for the time being.

254
00:16:44,434 --> 00:16:45,852
Leave as soon as you can.

255
00:16:49,772 --> 00:16:52,233
I'll take the small room.
You can take the big room.

256
00:16:56,779 --> 00:16:59,282
Wait, isn't that a given?

257
00:17:02,493 --> 00:17:04,120
How brazen.

258
00:17:11,127 --> 00:17:13,212
Take a look at the shower head.
It's leaking again.

259
00:17:14,631 --> 00:17:15,757
Okay, I will.

260
00:17:17,925 --> 00:17:19,427
You say that and do nothing.

261
00:17:20,803 --> 00:17:21,846
Goodness.

262
00:17:22,639 --> 00:17:25,933
Did you read about Zone F online?

263
00:17:27,685 --> 00:17:29,145
Yes, I did.

264
00:17:31,105 --> 00:17:32,690
Some people have too much energy.

265
00:17:33,274 --> 00:17:36,027
They do something at work
that we don't even do in bed.

266
00:17:53,878 --> 00:17:54,921
Shall we do it?

267
00:18:00,009 --> 00:18:01,511
I'm tired.

268
00:18:06,224 --> 00:18:07,809
I wasn't interested, either.

269
00:18:09,227 --> 00:18:10,269
Turn off the light.

270
00:18:10,603 --> 00:18:11,854
You do it.

271
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:31,165
You've lost weight.
Your face got smaller.

272
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,335
Are you stressed out
because of Joo In-a?

273
00:18:36,337 --> 00:18:38,005
Drink the whiskey you brought.

274
00:18:38,089 --> 00:18:39,257
Don't touch my beer.

275
00:18:40,675 --> 00:18:42,218
Do you hate her that much?

276
00:18:43,636 --> 00:18:44,679
Why?

277
00:18:44,971 --> 00:18:46,431
Because she made you handle affairs?

278
00:18:46,514 --> 00:18:48,307
They're PM cases, not affairs.

279
00:18:49,225 --> 00:18:51,811
Ms. Joo doesn't know about me yet.

280
00:18:51,894 --> 00:18:53,771
I was working on something
on Team One.

281
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:57,233
I put everything in the folder
and when she sees that

282
00:18:58,526 --> 00:19:00,528
she'll see how good I am
and reappoint me.

283
00:19:00,611 --> 00:19:01,779
If she's that competent.

284
00:19:03,823 --> 00:19:04,907
Think about it.

285
00:19:05,199 --> 00:19:07,910
She wouldn't want to waste
talent like mine on stupid cases.

286
00:19:07,994 --> 00:19:10,371
Why not? I think
you're perfect for the job.

287
00:19:10,913 --> 00:19:12,498
To handle the PM cheaters.

288
00:19:12,582 --> 00:19:13,958
Why me?

289
00:19:16,419 --> 00:19:17,879
- Hang on.
- You are

290
00:19:18,212 --> 00:19:19,589
the best one for the job.

291
00:19:22,717 --> 00:19:23,760
Hey.

292
00:19:25,052 --> 00:19:27,346
That's exactly what Joo In-a said,
that I was the best for the job.

293
00:19:28,347 --> 00:19:30,892
- Why am I best for the job?
- It's about couples in love.

294
00:19:31,601 --> 00:19:34,604
- That's your expertise.
- What does she know about me?

295
00:19:35,438 --> 00:19:37,482
We just met. She can't know...

296
00:19:39,692 --> 00:19:40,735
No way.

297
00:19:41,486 --> 00:19:42,570
That retreating figure...

298
00:19:47,074 --> 00:19:48,201
Did she see me?

299
00:19:51,037 --> 00:19:52,914
So the reason she chose me...

300
00:19:54,916 --> 00:19:55,958
was that?

301
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,671
No, it can't be.

302
00:20:02,715 --> 00:20:03,758
Can it be?

303
00:20:05,593 --> 00:20:06,594
Is it?

304
00:20:08,304 --> 00:20:09,472
Long, straight hair.

305
00:20:10,765 --> 00:20:11,891
A white shirt.

306
00:20:19,774 --> 00:20:21,025
It's practically a uniform.

307
00:20:40,211 --> 00:20:41,295
I can't say for sure.

308
00:20:42,505 --> 00:20:43,673
I don't think it was her.

309
00:20:51,514 --> 00:20:52,849
Why were you staring at me?

310
00:20:54,141 --> 00:20:55,393
Is a ghost haunting me?

311
00:20:55,476 --> 00:20:56,853
I came to make myself some coffee.

312
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,816
You look like
you have something to say.

313
00:21:02,149 --> 00:21:03,276
Mr. Noh.

314
00:21:03,359 --> 00:21:05,778
If you have any concerns,
you can come to me freely.

315
00:21:07,321 --> 00:21:09,532
Yes, rather than driving myself crazy

316
00:21:09,615 --> 00:21:10,783
I'll ask her and clear the air.

317
00:21:11,325 --> 00:21:13,035
- Ms. Joo.
- Wait.

318
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:17,790
I can't ask if she saw me kiss.

319
00:21:19,709 --> 00:21:20,710
What is it?

320
00:21:22,378 --> 00:21:24,005
What should we do
about the basement parking lot?

321
00:21:24,088 --> 00:21:27,675
We've confirmed through our humint
that it's a real issue.

322
00:21:28,050 --> 00:21:30,595
Shall we put up a sign saying
personal misconduct isn't allowed?

323
00:21:30,678 --> 00:21:31,888
We can't say we did any work, then.

324
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:34,640
- We have to expose them.
- Expose?

325
00:21:34,849 --> 00:21:36,642
How am I going to do that?

326
00:21:36,726 --> 00:21:38,436
I can't go on a stakeout
just to wait for it.

327
00:21:38,519 --> 00:21:39,520
A stakeout?

328
00:21:39,854 --> 00:21:41,105
A stakeout?

329
00:21:41,439 --> 00:21:43,900
Why would you say something
so nonsensical?

330
00:21:43,983 --> 00:21:47,194
We're not detectives.
Why would we go on a stakeout?

331
00:21:47,987 --> 00:21:50,072
- Right, exactly.
- Exactly.

332
00:21:50,406 --> 00:21:52,408
I heard that someone
on the Audit Team

333
00:21:52,491 --> 00:21:54,827
flew a drone and took photos.

334
00:21:55,161 --> 00:21:59,081
How could an auditor do that?
We're not some drone-flying club.

335
00:22:04,879 --> 00:22:06,297
Down your coffee and get moving.

336
00:22:07,423 --> 00:22:08,799
My poor legs.

337
00:22:11,218 --> 00:22:14,680
This was the only company car
left for us to take.

338
00:22:15,765 --> 00:22:18,392
Darn it. I should've brought my car.

339
00:22:18,851 --> 00:22:21,354
Still, if you push the seat
back a bit

340
00:22:21,437 --> 00:22:22,647
it should free up some space.

341
00:22:22,730 --> 00:22:24,482
- No, it's fine.
- Let me help you.

342
00:22:24,774 --> 00:22:26,317
It's fine, really. I...

343
00:22:29,904 --> 00:22:31,530
I'm so sorry, Mr. Noh.

344
00:22:48,214 --> 00:22:50,091
Jeez, what the heck
are we even doing?

345
00:22:51,092 --> 00:22:52,760
Okay, Hyun-kyu.

346
00:22:53,135 --> 00:22:56,305
You didn't do all that studying
for your degree

347
00:22:57,098 --> 00:22:58,933
just to do this kind of job, did you?

348
00:23:00,559 --> 00:23:04,063
Unlike you,
I didn't go to a good university

349
00:23:04,146 --> 00:23:05,898
nor have great credentials.

350
00:23:07,024 --> 00:23:08,776
I barely got this job
because I'm from the area

351
00:23:08,859 --> 00:23:10,319
where Haemu built a huge factory.

352
00:23:10,778 --> 00:23:12,446
Oh, during my interview I said

353
00:23:13,197 --> 00:23:14,740
"White blood runs through my veins."

354
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:18,411
That's how I introduced myself,
and they liked how I was different.

355
00:23:20,913 --> 00:23:23,040
- "White blood."
- White blood.

356
00:23:24,542 --> 00:23:26,252
- By white, you meant Haemu's color?
- Yes.

357
00:23:26,877 --> 00:23:28,671
That's why they call you
"White Blood Cell."

358
00:23:28,754 --> 00:23:29,755
That's right.

359
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:37,054
You know, competent people like you

360
00:23:37,138 --> 00:23:40,099
might feel bored
by what our team does.

361
00:23:40,182 --> 00:23:43,352
But working at Haemu
which everyone envies

362
00:23:43,436 --> 00:23:48,024
and being on the Audit Team,
the best team in the company

363
00:23:48,315 --> 00:23:50,443
makes me pleased and proud.

364
00:24:04,707 --> 00:24:05,916
Hey, White Blood Cell.

365
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:07,376
Yes, Mr. Noh?

366
00:24:08,127 --> 00:24:10,629
I didn't doze off.
I was only blinking for a long time.

367
00:24:10,713 --> 00:24:11,756
Do you remember

368
00:24:12,423 --> 00:24:13,924
the day Ms. Joo first joined?

369
00:24:18,596 --> 00:24:20,931
Do you know what she was wearing?

370
00:24:21,891 --> 00:24:23,184
Just a moment.

371
00:24:23,726 --> 00:24:26,520
- I remember such details perfectly.
- Do you?

372
00:24:27,772 --> 00:24:29,148
See if you can remember.

373
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:31,734
What was she wearing?

374
00:24:33,069 --> 00:24:34,195
She wore

375
00:24:36,155 --> 00:24:37,323
black pants.

376
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:41,744
What about her top?

377
00:24:42,203 --> 00:24:43,245
Her top...

378
00:24:44,789 --> 00:24:45,831
It was black.

379
00:24:47,291 --> 00:24:48,584
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

380
00:24:51,212 --> 00:24:52,254
It was black.

381
00:24:55,466 --> 00:24:56,509
Or not.

382
00:24:57,927 --> 00:24:59,512
I think it was a white shirt.

383
00:25:00,763 --> 00:25:01,764
Hey.

384
00:25:03,182 --> 00:25:04,183
Are you saying she wore white?

385
00:25:06,310 --> 00:25:07,394
Maybe not.

386
00:25:07,937 --> 00:25:09,772
- What?
- Was it black?

387
00:25:10,689 --> 00:25:12,733
- Was it black?
- No.

388
00:25:13,818 --> 00:25:14,860
It was white.

389
00:25:15,444 --> 00:25:16,487
Yes, white.

390
00:25:17,571 --> 00:25:18,697
Why, you!

391
00:25:21,117 --> 00:25:22,159
It was definitely white.

392
00:25:23,577 --> 00:25:24,662
Am I mistaken?

393
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:27,164
Forget I even asked.

394
00:25:27,957 --> 00:25:31,043
- I'll go get coffee, so sober up.
- Okay.

395
00:25:59,238 --> 00:26:01,448
I have a bad feeling about this.

396
00:26:04,827 --> 00:26:06,579
Gosh, what am I even doing?

397
00:26:07,621 --> 00:26:09,957
So what if she saw it? I don't care.

398
00:26:10,416 --> 00:26:13,460
It's not like I committed a crime.
Forget it.

399
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,462
Oh, my gosh.

400
00:26:17,923 --> 00:26:19,175
Why are you so startled?

401
00:26:22,678 --> 00:26:24,054
You walked in so suddenly.

402
00:26:26,015 --> 00:26:27,850
Can't I walk in suddenly?

403
00:26:28,434 --> 00:26:30,102
Should I have knocked?

404
00:26:32,980 --> 00:26:34,064
What?

405
00:26:34,648 --> 00:26:35,649
Were you

406
00:26:37,776 --> 00:26:38,944
doing this again?

407
00:26:57,546 --> 00:26:58,631
What was that?

408
00:27:00,799 --> 00:27:03,344
So she saw it. She saw everything.

409
00:27:42,675 --> 00:27:43,717
Noh Ki-jun.

410
00:27:45,469 --> 00:27:46,553
What do you want?

411
00:27:47,096 --> 00:27:48,597
You told me to ignore you at work.

412
00:27:48,681 --> 00:27:50,140
It's just us now.

413
00:27:50,808 --> 00:27:52,434
Is it Joo In-a again?

414
00:27:52,726 --> 00:27:53,852
You look half-dead.

415
00:27:53,936 --> 00:27:54,937
Yes.

416
00:27:55,479 --> 00:27:57,273
Bury me on a sunny slope.

417
00:27:58,232 --> 00:27:59,692
Why are you thinking
of getting buried?

418
00:28:00,317 --> 00:28:01,610
You have a lifeline.

419
00:28:02,152 --> 00:28:03,237
Director Kim.

420
00:28:04,113 --> 00:28:06,282
His dinner with the VP got canceled

421
00:28:06,365 --> 00:28:07,992
and he seemed to be looking
for a drinking buddy.

422
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:25,843
Hello, Director Kim.

423
00:28:26,593 --> 00:28:28,762
It's Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

424
00:28:36,478 --> 00:28:41,191
Ms. Joo talks back
to every senior executive.

425
00:28:41,442 --> 00:28:44,028
Does she think I'm staying still
because I can't speak up?

426
00:28:44,445 --> 00:28:47,323
- I'm just keeping my boundaries.
- Yes, you're right.

427
00:28:48,324 --> 00:28:49,908
Is she rude to the executives, too?

428
00:28:50,743 --> 00:28:53,912
I guess she's not the type
to bow to the powerful.

429
00:28:53,996 --> 00:28:58,584
I don't care how she treats
the powerful or powerless.

430
00:28:59,752 --> 00:29:00,836
And there's you.

431
00:29:00,919 --> 00:29:03,297
She has such
a poor judgment of character.

432
00:29:03,756 --> 00:29:06,759
You're our ace, Mr. Noh.

433
00:29:06,842 --> 00:29:08,802
Yet she dumped you in Team Three.

434
00:29:09,219 --> 00:29:12,181
Now, you're handling PM cases.
What the heck is PM, anyway?

435
00:29:12,264 --> 00:29:13,265
Exactly.

436
00:29:13,932 --> 00:29:15,893
I'm having the worst time, sir.

437
00:29:16,226 --> 00:29:18,979
Don't you worry about that.

438
00:29:19,897 --> 00:29:20,898
You know who I am.

439
00:29:21,899 --> 00:29:24,193
Let me tell you something

440
00:29:24,651 --> 00:29:26,570
that's still off the record.

441
00:29:32,659 --> 00:29:35,788
I'm working to create
a new department.

442
00:29:37,206 --> 00:29:43,837
It'll serve as the control tower
of the whole organization.

443
00:29:44,838 --> 00:29:47,132
Business General... No.

444
00:29:47,216 --> 00:29:50,260
It's called
the General Business Control HQ.

445
00:29:50,344 --> 00:29:52,971
General Business Control HQ.

446
00:29:54,306 --> 00:29:56,141
- What a great name.
- Right?

447
00:29:57,810 --> 00:29:59,937
I said I wanted you on the team.

448
00:30:00,771 --> 00:30:03,565
You'll be able to escape soon.

449
00:30:08,028 --> 00:30:10,280
- Let me pour you a drink, sir.
- Okay.

450
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,827
A toast

451
00:30:15,494 --> 00:30:18,414
to our General Business

452
00:30:18,497 --> 00:30:20,624
- Control HQ.
- Control HQ.

453
00:30:20,791 --> 00:30:24,128
- Let's drink to its bright future.
- Cheers!

454
00:30:33,345 --> 00:30:34,555
I'm in the mood.

455
00:30:48,777 --> 00:30:49,862
I'm heading home.

456
00:30:49,945 --> 00:30:51,530
Bye. See you tomorrow.

457
00:30:55,451 --> 00:30:57,703
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM
ASSISTANT MANAGER KWON HYUN-WOO

458
00:30:57,786 --> 00:30:59,121
It's raining.

459
00:30:59,204 --> 00:31:00,247
When do you get off work?

460
00:31:03,834 --> 00:31:04,877
I'm working late.

461
00:31:05,252 --> 00:31:06,545
Buy an umbrella and head home.

462
00:31:25,689 --> 00:31:26,857
Hello?

463
00:31:30,736 --> 00:31:31,737
Jun-seo?

464
00:31:34,031 --> 00:31:35,491
We did that all the time.

465
00:31:36,450 --> 00:31:37,576
Back then...

466
00:31:38,869 --> 00:31:40,162
we were young and rash.

467
00:31:40,746 --> 00:31:41,914
I'm glad I called you.

468
00:31:50,172 --> 00:31:52,132
Are you sure
you don't need to eat dinner?

469
00:31:52,591 --> 00:31:54,343
You love to eat.

470
00:31:55,052 --> 00:31:56,803
I'm okay with anything
if I'm with you.

471
00:32:01,141 --> 00:32:02,184
Right.

472
00:32:07,272 --> 00:32:08,649
It's pouring.

473
00:32:17,783 --> 00:32:19,451
- Why don't we...
- Yes?

474
00:32:20,118 --> 00:32:21,161
stay together?

475
00:32:22,371 --> 00:32:23,622
Just until the rain stops.

476
00:32:53,944 --> 00:32:55,279
SEND
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM, KWON HYUN-WOO

477
00:32:58,282 --> 00:32:59,449
Sent.

478
00:33:01,159 --> 00:33:02,494
Great work.

479
00:33:02,828 --> 00:33:04,246
My gosh. You must be tired.

480
00:33:04,496 --> 00:33:05,622
Great work until late.

481
00:33:05,706 --> 00:33:08,083
Don't mention it. I'm feeling proud.

482
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:10,168
Today was
the first overtime of my life.

483
00:33:11,086 --> 00:33:12,087
Really?

484
00:33:12,713 --> 00:33:13,755
In that case

485
00:33:14,256 --> 00:33:15,507
why don't we grab a drink
to celebrate?

486
00:33:15,591 --> 00:33:16,883
I'd love to.

487
00:33:17,175 --> 00:33:18,468
Let's eat
something delicious, Mr. Kwon.

488
00:33:18,552 --> 00:33:20,470
- Okay, let's wrap up and leave.
- Great!

489
00:33:29,354 --> 00:33:30,689
WIFE

490
00:33:41,366 --> 00:33:42,743
I said you could leave first.

491
00:33:46,330 --> 00:33:47,372
Were you rained on?

492
00:33:54,338 --> 00:33:55,589
We shouldn't do this.

493
00:34:00,844 --> 00:34:02,262
The rain has stopped.

494
00:34:04,556 --> 00:34:05,557
Let's do it.

495
00:34:06,099 --> 00:34:07,684
- What?
- Let's do it.

496
00:34:09,144 --> 00:34:10,646
We can't keep going like this.
We have to do it.

497
00:34:11,271 --> 00:34:12,481
What's with you?

498
00:34:15,192 --> 00:34:17,486
All right. Let's go home first.
You're going to catch a cold.

499
00:34:18,654 --> 00:34:19,696
Let's do it here.

500
00:34:20,155 --> 00:34:21,948
It's that area. Zone F.

501
00:34:32,542 --> 00:34:33,543
Hey.

502
00:34:40,092 --> 00:34:41,718
- What's with you?
- Be quiet.

503
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:23,635
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

504
00:35:23,719 --> 00:35:25,262
The president approved!

505
00:35:25,345 --> 00:35:28,014
You'll be out of the Audit Team
within days, Mr. Noh.

506
00:35:28,098 --> 00:35:30,559
Director Kim, you're awesome!

507
00:35:34,229 --> 00:35:36,440
I'm the best

508
00:35:37,941 --> 00:35:39,693
I'm the best

509
00:35:40,986 --> 00:35:43,071
- Are you getting off early today?
- I'll try to.

510
00:35:43,405 --> 00:35:44,614
- Let's eat something good.
- Okay.

511
00:35:44,990 --> 00:35:46,908
- Try to clock out quickly.
- Okay.

512
00:35:51,747 --> 00:35:54,124
- Hello. Good morning.
- Hello.

513
00:35:59,254 --> 00:36:01,506
- The weather's great, isn't it?
- Yes.

514
00:36:02,424 --> 00:36:05,051
You're looking extra sharp today.

515
00:36:05,761 --> 00:36:06,970
- Do I?
- Yes.

516
00:36:07,721 --> 00:36:09,681
You two look great, too.

517
00:36:11,016 --> 00:36:12,434
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

518
00:36:24,905 --> 00:36:25,906
Hello, Ms. Joo.

519
00:36:26,490 --> 00:36:27,949
Hey, Mr. Noh. Good morning.

520
00:36:28,408 --> 00:36:30,744
You must like dress shirts.
You look good in them.

521
00:36:32,829 --> 00:36:34,039
You're looking happy.

522
00:36:34,498 --> 00:36:36,041
Did something great happen
this morning?

523
00:36:36,291 --> 00:36:38,210
There's no reason
to be in a foul mood.

524
00:36:38,293 --> 00:36:39,628
Look at that great weather.

525
00:36:39,711 --> 00:36:41,087
There is a reason, actually.

526
00:36:42,172 --> 00:36:44,299
You haven't caught
a single case in the parking garage.

527
00:36:45,425 --> 00:36:47,761
You won't take matters lightly
just like you did

528
00:36:47,844 --> 00:36:49,471
with Mr. Son's case, will you?

529
00:36:50,639 --> 00:36:51,681
Keep it up, will you?

530
00:36:51,765 --> 00:36:54,559
Every assignment is important
here in the Audit Team.

531
00:36:55,644 --> 00:36:58,855
Fine, I'll go along. I won't have
to see her for much longer.

532
00:36:59,147 --> 00:37:00,440
Yes, of course.

533
00:37:00,732 --> 00:37:03,068
I even brought my car
to stake out properly.

534
00:37:03,527 --> 00:37:05,153
Will I ever let you down again?

535
00:37:06,279 --> 00:37:07,447
No, never.

536
00:37:15,789 --> 00:37:16,873
Ms. Joo.

537
00:37:17,249 --> 00:37:20,335
There was a huge lucky draw
at our online mall recently

538
00:37:20,544 --> 00:37:23,129
and people are asking
how the winners were decided

539
00:37:23,213 --> 00:37:25,340
or if the draw was even real,
and some are complaining

540
00:37:25,423 --> 00:37:27,175
that they didn't win
even after many tries.

541
00:37:27,259 --> 00:37:29,970
It's not like the Audit Team
is the customer service center.

542
00:37:30,053 --> 00:37:32,806
Mr. Noh, you can continue
to work on the parking lot case.

543
00:37:33,139 --> 00:37:34,391
Wait a second.

544
00:37:34,850 --> 00:37:37,102
You'll need a partner
for your stakeout, won't you?

545
00:37:37,811 --> 00:37:39,688
Goodness. One second.

546
00:37:40,605 --> 00:37:43,233
White Blood Cell is on the phone too.
We don't have enough manpower.

547
00:37:44,818 --> 00:37:46,403
We do, Mr. Moo.

548
00:37:47,070 --> 00:37:48,738
We have our strongest asset here.

549
00:37:50,615 --> 00:37:51,616
Who?

550
00:37:59,875 --> 00:38:01,668
You're making me feel uncomfortable.
Cut it out.

551
00:38:04,087 --> 00:38:07,215
Why? Is the parking lot case
not quite suitable for you?

552
00:38:09,467 --> 00:38:12,762
But you told me that every case here
is equally important.

553
00:38:18,184 --> 00:38:19,352
Shall I do that, then?

554
00:38:20,103 --> 00:38:22,647
Let's spend some quality time alone.

555
00:38:30,906 --> 00:38:32,490
You don't need to buckle up.

556
00:38:33,366 --> 00:38:34,409
I'm not starting the car.

557
00:38:37,245 --> 00:38:38,371
It's my decision.

558
00:38:38,455 --> 00:38:40,165
Come on. You forgot, didn't you?

559
00:38:40,665 --> 00:38:42,375
Unbuckle it.
It must be uncomfortable.

560
00:38:42,459 --> 00:38:44,336
No, I'm not uncomfortable at all.

561
00:38:44,419 --> 00:38:46,463
I feel so comfortable right now.

562
00:38:46,546 --> 00:38:48,715
Unbuckle it. You don't need
to play it cool over this matter.

563
00:38:50,926 --> 00:38:52,260
Things happen.

564
00:38:52,636 --> 00:38:55,555
Stakeouts are for people
who are experienced.

565
00:38:55,764 --> 00:38:56,973
It's all right.

566
00:38:59,309 --> 00:39:02,896
I knew it. Your understanding
of these assignments is very high.

567
00:39:02,979 --> 00:39:03,980
Sorry?

568
00:39:05,231 --> 00:39:07,108
I'm sure you know a thing or two

569
00:39:07,192 --> 00:39:09,527
about cases like this one.

570
00:39:12,906 --> 00:39:13,949
Ms. Joo.

571
00:39:14,658 --> 00:39:17,786
- Back then, that...
- That? What do you mean by that?

572
00:39:17,869 --> 00:39:20,080
That. Whatever it is you saw.

573
00:39:20,455 --> 00:39:21,498
It wasn't that...

574
00:39:22,082 --> 00:39:24,376
I'm not that kind of person.

575
00:39:24,626 --> 00:39:26,419
My lips were also...

576
00:39:27,504 --> 00:39:28,546
Quiet.

577
00:39:30,006 --> 00:39:31,049
Over there.

578
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,241
Okay.

579
00:40:11,172 --> 00:40:13,466
I'll wrap it up. It's my job.

580
00:40:25,895 --> 00:40:28,148
I'll open the door.
I'm from the Audit Team.

581
00:40:37,115 --> 00:40:38,658
I'm opening the door.

582
00:40:46,416 --> 00:40:48,752
Oh, my. Director Kim!

583
00:40:49,252 --> 00:40:50,378
You said you were busy.

584
00:40:53,048 --> 00:40:55,425
- Wait.
- What are you two doing here?

585
00:40:55,508 --> 00:40:56,509
What's with you?

586
00:40:57,844 --> 00:41:00,305
You, of all people,
should know better.

587
00:41:00,388 --> 00:41:03,308
When you both have spouses,
don't you?

588
00:41:06,436 --> 00:41:08,730
Will you close that door?

589
00:41:09,773 --> 00:41:11,274
Wrap it up and come outside.

590
00:41:20,033 --> 00:41:21,493
I knew it, Mr. Noh.

591
00:41:21,743 --> 00:41:23,661
I knew you could do it!

592
00:41:24,245 --> 00:41:27,457
You caught a big one.
He's a big fish!

593
00:41:27,957 --> 00:41:30,126
This is why you're the ace
of the Audit Team.

594
00:41:31,294 --> 00:41:32,337
Let's see.

595
00:41:32,670 --> 00:41:36,049
Director Kim was
formerly your direct superior.

596
00:41:38,384 --> 00:41:41,221
You took down your former superior
whom you worked with for years

597
00:41:41,888 --> 00:41:43,723
like a cold-blooded man!

598
00:41:44,390 --> 00:41:46,017
If only everyone else were like you

599
00:41:46,101 --> 00:41:49,854
this world would've been
a much better place.

600
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:58,571
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

601
00:41:59,114 --> 00:42:01,866
Is there a possibility
that Director Kim will be let off

602
00:42:01,950 --> 00:42:04,285
- just like Mr. Son?
- No.

603
00:42:04,702 --> 00:42:06,579
This is a different case.

604
00:42:07,163 --> 00:42:09,707
He's an executive, so we can revoke
his contract and fire him right away.

605
00:42:09,791 --> 00:42:11,126
Fire him?

606
00:42:12,127 --> 00:42:14,712
But Director Kim is also
a necessary part of the company...

607
00:42:14,796 --> 00:42:16,214
Not at all.

608
00:42:16,548 --> 00:42:18,675
He's an old-timer with an ego
who sits around doing nothing

609
00:42:18,758 --> 00:42:20,135
only because
he's close to the president.

610
00:42:20,969 --> 00:42:22,720
He must've been an eyesore
to the vice president.

611
00:42:23,972 --> 00:42:27,559
You just gave him
a wonderful reason to fire that man.

612
00:42:32,897 --> 00:42:34,023
Director Kim

613
00:42:36,401 --> 00:42:37,402
is done for.

614
00:43:06,139 --> 00:43:08,516
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

615
00:43:11,227 --> 00:43:14,022
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to...

616
00:43:26,159 --> 00:43:28,953
ELDEST SISTER
ACCEPT

617
00:43:29,037 --> 00:43:30,705
- Hilarious.
- Hey.

618
00:43:31,247 --> 00:43:34,083
Hello, Ki-jun? When are you coming?

619
00:43:34,876 --> 00:43:36,836
I'm on my way, and I'm almost there.

620
00:43:41,382 --> 00:43:44,260
Ki-jun, we have to change
the bathroom doorknob, too.

621
00:43:44,552 --> 00:43:45,595
Okay.

622
00:43:47,222 --> 00:43:48,264
Hey, Ki-jun!

623
00:43:48,681 --> 00:43:50,475
Take a look at Jin-yeong's laptop.

624
00:43:51,059 --> 00:43:52,769
- Laptop?
- Hey, Ki-jun.

625
00:43:52,852 --> 00:43:54,354
That couch has been wobbling.
Take a look.

626
00:43:54,729 --> 00:43:57,565
I'm only one man,
so talk to me one at a time.

627
00:43:59,275 --> 00:44:00,276
The couch?

628
00:44:02,320 --> 00:44:04,113
- Which side is wobbly?
- The left.

629
00:44:04,197 --> 00:44:05,448
Goodness.

630
00:44:07,575 --> 00:44:11,204
Goodness, I'm so proud of you,
my youngest one.

631
00:44:13,873 --> 00:44:15,833
Cut it out, Mom.

632
00:44:22,090 --> 00:44:23,633
Mom, this meat is delicious.

633
00:44:27,262 --> 00:44:29,180
Hey, Ki-jun.
Why are you drinking so much?

634
00:44:29,264 --> 00:44:31,015
Look at him.
He hasn't even eaten his food.

635
00:44:31,099 --> 00:44:32,350
You can't even hold your alcohol.

636
00:44:33,518 --> 00:44:36,396
- Stop drinking.
- Stop pinching me, please!

637
00:44:37,105 --> 00:44:38,398
Will you just leave me alone?

638
00:44:38,481 --> 00:44:39,983
Is something going on, Ki-jun?

639
00:44:40,233 --> 00:44:41,526
Right? What's wrong?

640
00:44:42,193 --> 00:44:43,820
Hey, is someone bullying you?

641
00:44:44,862 --> 00:44:47,740
What? Hey, who is it?
Who's that punk?

642
00:44:47,824 --> 00:44:49,701
Hey, go file a lawsuit.

643
00:44:49,784 --> 00:44:51,452
- Talk to her husband!
- I'll talk to him.

644
00:44:51,536 --> 00:44:53,496
We have to talk it out first.
Do you want me to make a call?

645
00:44:53,579 --> 00:44:55,999
Please stop this and leave me alone.

646
00:44:56,082 --> 00:44:58,001
We need the name first. Who is it?

647
00:44:58,084 --> 00:45:00,128
- We have to talk it out first.
- Talk what out?

648
00:45:00,211 --> 00:45:02,005
Look at this kid.

649
00:45:02,088 --> 00:45:04,299
Call your husband first, okay?

650
00:45:04,382 --> 00:45:07,427
Who's the punk that did this
to my precious son?

651
00:45:08,136 --> 00:45:09,429
- You...
- Darn it.

652
00:45:09,512 --> 00:45:10,847
- Who is it?
- Talk it out.

653
00:45:10,930 --> 00:45:12,932
- Hey, tell me who it is.
- We need the name first.

654
00:45:13,016 --> 00:45:14,892
- What's the name?
- Mom, listen.

655
00:45:14,976 --> 00:45:17,061
- We need the name first.
- We need that.

656
00:45:17,145 --> 00:45:18,396
- Who is it?
- Why won't he pick up?

657
00:45:18,479 --> 00:45:19,772
- Get the name.
- We need the name.

658
00:45:19,856 --> 00:45:21,232
You all need to stop.

659
00:45:21,316 --> 00:45:23,109
- Who is it? Tell me!
- Hear me out.

660
00:45:23,192 --> 00:45:25,987
- Ki-jun.
- I hate all three of you!

661
00:45:26,070 --> 00:45:28,323
Just leave me alone!

662
00:45:28,406 --> 00:45:30,825
No, bring her phone to me.

663
00:45:31,034 --> 00:45:33,244
- Is he not picking up?
- Call the customer service line.

664
00:45:33,328 --> 00:45:35,830
- The customer service?
- We need to reach someone!

665
00:45:50,970 --> 00:45:53,181
HAEMU PHARMACEUTICAL
2025 CONTRACT INSPECTION

666
00:45:53,264 --> 00:45:54,974
2024 FUND EXECUTION INSPECTION

667
00:45:58,353 --> 00:46:00,021
NOH KI-JUN, AUDIT TEAM 1 TURNOVER

668
00:46:00,104 --> 00:46:04,817
DO YOU WISH TO PERMANENTLY DELETE
ALL FOLDERS AND FILES?

669
00:46:24,587 --> 00:46:27,131
I'm sorry about Director Kim.

670
00:46:27,215 --> 00:46:29,300
- Did you dig him up intentionally?
- No.

671
00:46:30,259 --> 00:46:31,719
It was a coincidence
from another case.

672
00:46:31,803 --> 00:46:32,804
How disappointing.

673
00:46:33,096 --> 00:46:34,806
I thought you finally learned
to wield your sword

674
00:46:34,889 --> 00:46:36,015
but it was sheer luck.

675
00:46:37,308 --> 00:46:39,185
I haven't given you anything yet.

676
00:46:39,852 --> 00:46:40,895
Prove yourself

677
00:46:41,604 --> 00:46:42,897
that you're different from your mom.

678
00:47:06,629 --> 00:47:08,923
Honey, Sung-yeol is here.

679
00:47:10,299 --> 00:47:12,510
You should say hi to him.
I'll go and make coffee.

680
00:47:15,304 --> 00:47:17,140
Father, your youngest son is here.

681
00:47:18,808 --> 00:47:21,477
- And so are you, Jae-yeol.
- It's been a while.

682
00:47:23,938 --> 00:47:25,273
How's your health, Father?

683
00:47:25,815 --> 00:47:27,984
I've exiled you
and haven't called you back.

684
00:47:28,401 --> 00:47:30,027
How dare you show yourself here?

685
00:47:30,111 --> 00:47:31,737
It's great to see
that you're the same.

686
00:47:34,449 --> 00:47:36,534
How come there is
no middle ground between you two?

687
00:47:36,951 --> 00:47:39,287
One of you is too soft
to do anything substantial

688
00:47:39,620 --> 00:47:43,124
and the other is too reckless,
causing trouble everywhere.

689
00:47:43,541 --> 00:47:44,542
Darn it.

690
00:47:46,127 --> 00:47:48,254
You see, Father

691
00:47:49,255 --> 00:47:50,756
I have caused yet another trouble.

692
00:47:52,467 --> 00:47:54,969
It's the gas plant in Saudi Arabia
that you've even dreamed of.

693
00:47:55,052 --> 00:47:58,055
I got the first package,
and on top of that the third one.

694
00:47:58,389 --> 00:48:01,100
The entire project
is worth 8.77 billion dollars.

695
00:48:02,018 --> 00:48:03,144
And I got it.

696
00:48:10,359 --> 00:48:13,279
So? Isn't this good enough
to put an end to my exile?

697
00:48:14,614 --> 00:48:16,574
I hear there's a spot open
in the head office.

698
00:48:32,965 --> 00:48:34,300
Should I cancel the luncheon?

699
00:48:34,675 --> 00:48:36,135
You do not look well.

700
00:48:37,386 --> 00:48:38,429
I'm fine.

701
00:48:41,015 --> 00:48:42,975
I need personnel evaluation reports

702
00:48:43,476 --> 00:48:45,186
and a list of potential staff
up for a promotion.

703
00:48:45,978 --> 00:48:47,021
Also, set up

704
00:48:47,563 --> 00:48:50,483
a dinner with QS International's
President Lee Hyeong-geun

705
00:48:50,858 --> 00:48:51,859
as soon as possible.

706
00:48:52,401 --> 00:48:53,611
I understand.

707
00:48:54,904 --> 00:48:57,406
Would you like to leave right away
for the AI camp?

708
00:48:58,491 --> 00:48:59,492
In half an hour.

709
00:49:01,827 --> 00:49:02,912
One second.

710
00:49:25,017 --> 00:49:26,477
I can do this for myself.

711
00:49:28,104 --> 00:49:29,272
E-mail me the files.

712
00:49:32,858 --> 00:49:33,859
Yes, sir.

713
00:50:11,772 --> 00:50:14,150
- What now?
- I'm telling you.

714
00:50:17,361 --> 00:50:18,904
Goodness, I need some sugar.

715
00:50:21,866 --> 00:50:22,867
My gosh.

716
00:50:24,785 --> 00:50:27,747
Where was Ms. Yoon's snack box again?

717
00:50:29,248 --> 00:50:31,250
There it is. Ms. Yoon's snack box.

718
00:50:32,418 --> 00:50:35,588
Goodness. It's heavy.
Did you get something new?

719
00:50:36,964 --> 00:50:38,549
Hey, these are new.

720
00:50:42,678 --> 00:50:43,679
It's good.

721
00:50:45,014 --> 00:50:46,057
- Mango-flavored?
- Yes.

722
00:50:46,390 --> 00:50:48,809
Hey, Hae-young. Where are we
having team dinner again?

723
00:50:48,893 --> 00:50:50,353
Piggy's Charcoal BBQ.

724
00:50:50,436 --> 00:50:51,437
We're having pork again?

725
00:50:51,937 --> 00:50:54,607
Can we get something better?
It's Ms. Joo's welcome party.

726
00:50:54,690 --> 00:50:56,984
Our budget for team dinners
is running low this year.

727
00:50:57,276 --> 00:50:58,736
Ms. Pyun.

728
00:50:59,153 --> 00:51:01,322
Why do you act like
a stingy mother-in-law

729
00:51:01,405 --> 00:51:04,158
who never lets anyone near her money
with the company fund?

730
00:51:05,284 --> 00:51:07,453
There's a servant
that's trying to clean out the fund

731
00:51:07,787 --> 00:51:09,121
so I have no other choice, Mr. Moo.

732
00:51:09,205 --> 00:51:10,206
- What?
- Servant?

733
00:51:10,539 --> 00:51:11,582
You heard her, right?

734
00:51:11,666 --> 00:51:13,125
Did you just call me a servant?

735
00:51:13,209 --> 00:51:15,878
- Do you feel guilty?
- Technically, we're all servants.

736
00:51:16,879 --> 00:51:17,963
Anyway.

737
00:51:18,547 --> 00:51:20,174
Where's Mr. Noh?
He's been away for a while.

738
00:51:20,257 --> 00:51:22,718
Mr. Noh didn't seem well.

739
00:51:22,802 --> 00:51:25,596
He doesn't look well,
he keeps sighing

740
00:51:25,971 --> 00:51:28,641
and his eyes looked a bit watery too.

741
00:51:29,225 --> 00:51:31,644
- Anyway, he looks quite sad.
- Really?

742
00:51:32,728 --> 00:51:34,897
- Did he get dumped?
- I think so.

743
00:51:34,980 --> 00:51:37,108
Goodness. That's heartbreaking.

744
00:51:41,654 --> 00:51:43,030
Thanks a lot.

745
00:52:03,300 --> 00:52:04,343
He is

746
00:52:04,969 --> 00:52:06,053
leaving.

747
00:52:11,726 --> 00:52:12,852
My hope.

748
00:52:14,228 --> 00:52:15,438
My lifeline.

749
00:52:18,441 --> 00:52:19,567
Adios.

750
00:52:20,943 --> 00:52:22,570
PIGGY'S CHARCOAL BBQ

751
00:52:22,653 --> 00:52:23,654
Hello.

752
00:52:23,863 --> 00:52:25,030
Thank you.

753
00:52:31,412 --> 00:52:33,831
It used to be a great spot.

754
00:52:34,832 --> 00:52:36,834
Back then, the front of the factory
used to be salt farms.

755
00:52:36,917 --> 00:52:38,586
It became a huge issue.

756
00:52:38,669 --> 00:52:40,921
What's the most important
when it comes to making salt?

757
00:52:41,005 --> 00:52:42,089
Sunlight and wind.

758
00:52:42,757 --> 00:52:44,717
So if the southeastern direction
gets blocked off

759
00:52:45,259 --> 00:52:47,595
it creates a shadow
and stops the wind

760
00:52:47,678 --> 00:52:48,971
which stops salt from crystallizing.

761
00:52:49,638 --> 00:52:52,725
And the one who stepped up
as a troubleshooter was...

762
00:52:52,808 --> 00:52:53,893
Mr. Baek.

763
00:52:54,518 --> 00:52:57,480
- You should eat some, too.
- I've been eating. It's okay.

764
00:52:57,688 --> 00:53:00,941
You're making me look rude.

765
00:53:01,025 --> 00:53:02,234
After all, I'm the youngest.

766
00:53:03,903 --> 00:53:05,571
No, it's all right, really.

767
00:53:06,030 --> 00:53:08,616
Because everyone thinks
you're just like that.

768
00:53:08,699 --> 00:53:09,992
That I'm just rude?

769
00:53:11,744 --> 00:53:12,828
That wasn't what I meant.

770
00:53:13,996 --> 00:53:15,664
The meat is burning. Have some.

771
00:53:16,207 --> 00:53:18,959
- And Mr. Oh is such an odd guy.
- You just dissed me.

772
00:53:19,043 --> 00:53:22,171
This happened during the early days
of his time in China.

773
00:53:22,254 --> 00:53:23,255
Really?

774
00:53:24,006 --> 00:53:25,716
What do you mean?
I haven't said anything.

775
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:27,843
- I can't believe it.
- Wait, it's not that.

776
00:53:28,052 --> 00:53:30,262
Will you listen up?
Anyway, this guy...

777
00:53:30,805 --> 00:53:31,972
All right.

778
00:53:32,181 --> 00:53:34,975
Audit Team Three,
why don't we make a toast?

779
00:53:35,059 --> 00:53:36,769
Hello, Ms. Joo.

780
00:53:37,603 --> 00:53:38,896
Thank you.

781
00:53:39,897 --> 00:53:42,983
- Shall we have a toast?
- One second, please.

782
00:53:43,275 --> 00:53:44,360
Goodness.

783
00:53:45,528 --> 00:53:47,363
- Yes, drink up.
- I will.

784
00:53:47,446 --> 00:53:49,073
We're all here
to make a living, aren't we?

785
00:53:49,156 --> 00:53:50,449
- Thank you.
- Sure.

786
00:53:51,075 --> 00:53:53,202
- Now, would you like a drink?
- Yes, Ms. Joo.

787
00:53:53,369 --> 00:53:55,412
- Drink up.
- Thank you.

788
00:53:59,416 --> 00:54:01,168
Mr. Noh, why don't you
have a drink, too?

789
00:54:08,217 --> 00:54:09,510
You want soju?

790
00:54:10,177 --> 00:54:11,220
Okay.

791
00:54:12,429 --> 00:54:14,932
You've done well, Mr. Noh.

792
00:54:17,434 --> 00:54:19,854
You all know
that Mr. Noh got someone big, right?

793
00:54:19,937 --> 00:54:20,938
Yes, of course.

794
00:54:21,021 --> 00:54:22,773
Mr. Noh is the pride of our team!

795
00:54:22,857 --> 00:54:25,609
He says you're the pride.

796
00:54:26,360 --> 00:54:28,612
Why don't we make a toast to Mr. Noh,
the ace of Audit Team Three?

797
00:54:28,904 --> 00:54:30,531
- Shall we?
- Goodness.

798
00:54:30,614 --> 00:54:31,824
All right.

799
00:54:32,575 --> 00:54:34,493
To Mr. Noh.

800
00:54:34,577 --> 00:54:36,620
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

801
00:54:36,704 --> 00:54:38,581
- Cheers!
- All right, Mr. Noh!

802
00:54:41,208 --> 00:54:42,501
That's nice.

803
00:54:43,419 --> 00:54:44,420
Gosh.

804
00:54:45,212 --> 00:54:47,214
That's a nice drink.

805
00:54:47,923 --> 00:54:48,966
May I?

806
00:54:50,259 --> 00:54:51,302
A lettuce wrap, Ms. Joo.

807
00:54:51,385 --> 00:54:54,430
I need you baby, bye bye bye

808
00:54:54,513 --> 00:54:58,100
Must you go, why why why?

809
00:54:58,183 --> 00:55:01,020
All you said was a lie lie lie

810
00:55:01,103 --> 00:55:03,939
I will wait

811
00:55:04,023 --> 00:55:07,526
Until the day I die

812
00:55:08,027 --> 00:55:13,198
Do not cry alone
Because I am not there

813
00:55:14,241 --> 00:55:16,785
Goodbye

814
00:55:19,997 --> 00:55:23,042
Come back

815
00:55:23,125 --> 00:55:26,921
My dear

816
00:55:28,005 --> 00:55:31,550
Do you not know

817
00:55:32,176 --> 00:55:34,219
- These songs are killing the vibe.
- Right?

818
00:55:35,763 --> 00:55:39,224
May I resuscitate the mood
as the head of this organization?

819
00:55:41,185 --> 00:55:43,062
Drop that microphone now.

820
00:55:44,229 --> 00:55:46,315
Come back here, Mr. Noh.

821
00:55:46,982 --> 00:55:49,276
It's "Twit"!

822
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:50,361
Okay!

823
00:55:59,453 --> 00:56:00,913
You're a fool

824
00:56:02,039 --> 00:56:03,958
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

825
00:56:04,041 --> 00:56:05,292
I don't like it

826
00:56:05,376 --> 00:56:07,962
Nobody likes it
The delicate Sim Cheong

827
00:56:09,088 --> 00:56:11,090
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

828
00:56:11,173 --> 00:56:13,968
I don't like it
Nobody likes it

829
00:56:14,301 --> 00:56:15,719
You're a fool

830
00:56:16,720 --> 00:56:18,931
All you care about is yourself

831
00:56:20,015 --> 00:56:23,519
The delicate Sim Cheong

832
00:56:23,727 --> 00:56:24,979
Try to look around

833
00:56:25,688 --> 00:56:28,524
You're in pain but you have no idea

834
00:56:28,983 --> 00:56:30,651
You make me royal
You make me a hero

835
00:56:30,734 --> 00:56:32,069
You make me a genius, yes

836
00:56:32,361 --> 00:56:35,614
You give a lot
But why do you always end up unhappy?

837
00:56:35,990 --> 00:56:39,201
Because you only breathe for yourself

838
00:56:41,745 --> 00:56:43,205
You're a fool

839
00:56:43,288 --> 00:56:46,291
- Yeah! Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

840
00:56:46,375 --> 00:56:49,420
I don't like it
Nobody likes it

841
00:56:55,259 --> 00:56:56,468
Ms. Joo In-a.

842
00:56:57,594 --> 00:56:59,430
Don't you think this is too much?

843
00:57:06,520 --> 00:57:07,521
Fine.

844
00:57:08,355 --> 00:57:09,982
I kissed.

845
00:57:11,608 --> 00:57:14,319
I know that's why you put me
in charge of PM.

846
00:57:15,571 --> 00:57:17,072
But what's so bad about that?

847
00:57:18,073 --> 00:57:21,660
Why is that misconduct?

848
00:57:23,120 --> 00:57:24,747
Does anyone here never kiss?

849
00:57:25,706 --> 00:57:26,749
Ever?

850
00:57:26,832 --> 00:57:28,917
Don't you ever kiss?

851
00:57:29,334 --> 00:57:31,336
Don't you kiss, too?

852
00:58:24,598 --> 00:58:25,641
Are you okay?

853
00:58:26,016 --> 00:58:27,226
You threw up all night.

854
00:58:29,686 --> 00:58:30,979
I heard
you dropped a bomb last night.

855
00:58:31,605 --> 00:58:32,856
How did you know?

856
00:58:32,940 --> 00:58:34,274
We are a company.

857
00:58:34,358 --> 00:58:36,443
Something fun like that
goes around in real-time.

858
00:58:38,028 --> 00:58:39,947
You've never been
the object of hatred, have you?

859
00:58:40,322 --> 00:58:42,950
You're the beloved Noh Ki-jun,
whom everyone liked.

860
00:58:43,534 --> 00:58:44,701
Beloved, my foot.

861
00:58:50,624 --> 00:58:52,334
After all, it's just work.

862
00:58:53,085 --> 00:58:55,170
She'll forget someday
if I do my job well, right?

863
00:58:55,796 --> 00:58:56,797
Ki-jun.

864
00:58:57,297 --> 00:59:00,384
When you adore someone,
you adore them for no reason.

865
00:59:00,467 --> 00:59:03,512
But once you hate someone,
you hate them no matter what they do.

866
00:59:04,346 --> 00:59:07,474
I'm sure Ms. Joo thinks
you're her biggest eyesore right now

867
00:59:07,558 --> 00:59:08,559
no matter what you do.

868
00:59:09,768 --> 00:59:11,353
Should I just quit?

869
00:59:11,436 --> 00:59:13,272
You still need to get to work

870
00:59:13,814 --> 00:59:15,440
to turn in your resignation.

871
00:59:16,316 --> 00:59:17,484
I'm taking the day off.

872
00:59:18,443 --> 00:59:19,486
Good for you.

873
00:59:39,298 --> 00:59:40,716
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

874
00:59:41,884 --> 00:59:43,218
I apologize for last night.

875
00:59:43,427 --> 00:59:44,887
You must've been quite disappointed.

876
00:59:45,721 --> 00:59:46,722
Sorry?

877
00:59:49,683 --> 00:59:52,186
That you couldn't transfer
to General Business Control HQ.

878
00:59:55,439 --> 00:59:58,567
You should've talked to me
if you wanted to leave the team.

879
00:59:58,650 --> 01:00:00,194
I'm not that uptight.

880
01:00:01,111 --> 01:00:02,571
Instead of talking behind my back.

881
01:00:04,698 --> 01:00:07,534
Also, that department
is no longer in formation

882
01:00:07,618 --> 01:00:08,827
with Director Kim's dismissal.

883
01:00:18,837 --> 01:00:20,923
Are you feeling all right?

884
01:00:21,840 --> 01:00:23,342
I think

885
01:00:23,634 --> 01:00:26,136
you're really something, Mr. Noh.

886
01:00:26,345 --> 01:00:28,305
If I were you,
I could never come to work.

887
01:00:28,639 --> 01:00:30,557
Stop making matters worse.

888
01:00:31,516 --> 01:00:34,228
I'm sure it's hard enough for him.

889
01:00:34,478 --> 01:00:35,520
Isn't it?

890
01:00:38,232 --> 01:00:40,025
I guess he's the type who blows up.

891
01:00:48,909 --> 01:00:51,245
No, okay? That's not it.

892
01:01:03,215 --> 01:01:04,216
NOH KI-JUN

893
01:01:05,342 --> 01:01:07,010
CHECK SEVERANCE PAY

894
01:01:07,928 --> 01:01:09,596
SEVERANCE PAY: 40,788,560 WON

895
01:01:09,680 --> 01:01:10,681
All right.

896
01:01:10,889 --> 01:01:13,558
That's enough money
to last some time to get refreshed

897
01:01:13,642 --> 01:01:15,060
before I get another job.

898
01:01:16,144 --> 01:01:17,896
Dang it. I'll just quit.

899
01:01:20,065 --> 01:01:21,108
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

900
01:01:22,859 --> 01:01:24,236
NAME: NOH KI-JUN

901
01:01:24,319 --> 01:01:25,570
REQUESTED BY: NOH KI-JUN

902
01:01:38,250 --> 01:01:39,543
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

903
01:01:57,436 --> 01:01:59,062
Ms. Joo, I must talk to you.

904
01:02:01,565 --> 01:02:02,607
Mr. Noh.

905
01:02:03,025 --> 01:02:04,067
Mr. Noh!

906
01:02:07,446 --> 01:02:08,864
Did you take my printout?

907
01:02:10,615 --> 01:02:11,908
AUDIT TEAM 3 STATIONERY SPENDINGS

908
01:02:15,579 --> 01:02:16,580
One moment, please.

909
01:02:21,793 --> 01:02:22,919
Here.

910
01:02:40,228 --> 01:02:41,396
Jeez.

911
01:02:45,776 --> 01:02:47,611
YOU HAVE A NEW E-MAIL:
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

912
01:03:04,753 --> 01:03:06,797
HEAD OF AUDIT

913
01:03:07,464 --> 01:03:10,008
HEAD OF AUDIT JOO IN-A

914
01:03:15,055 --> 01:03:17,474
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

915
01:03:19,267 --> 01:03:22,979
MS. JOO IN-A IS INVOLVED

916
01:03:23,063 --> 01:03:27,526
IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

917
01:03:51,716 --> 01:03:54,636
FILING FOR LOVE

918
01:03:55,220 --> 01:03:58,098
GUEST APPEARANCES BY SHIN HYUN-SOO,
PYO YE-JIN, AND KIM JONG-TAE

919
01:04:24,332 --> 01:04:25,625
Did I get you?

920
01:04:26,460 --> 01:04:29,087
If that report turns out to be true

921
01:04:29,421 --> 01:04:32,007
that means I'll have what I need
to take Joo In-a down.

922
01:04:32,632 --> 01:04:33,675
- What?
- What is this?

923
01:04:33,758 --> 01:04:34,801
The Older Women Hunter?

924
01:04:34,885 --> 01:04:36,219
You need to stop, ma'am.

925
01:04:36,303 --> 01:04:37,929
Please leave immediately.

926
01:04:38,763 --> 01:04:40,307
Joo In-a couldn't possibly be
having an affair.

927
01:04:40,599 --> 01:04:43,226
Has she ever come with a man?

928
01:04:43,310 --> 01:04:45,479
Gosh, ten condoms?

929
01:04:45,562 --> 01:04:48,940
Our company is about to see
the biggest storm in history.

930
01:04:49,024 --> 01:04:51,985
What kind of person is Joo In-a?

931
01:05:04,998 --> 01:05:07,000
